                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">A. Taking patient vital signs</div>
                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">B. Administering medications under physician supervision</div>
                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="true">C. Performing surgical procedures</div>
                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">D. Scheduling patient appointments</div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="quiz-question">
                                <p><strong>2. What is the difference between scope of practice and standards of care?</strong></p>
                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">A. They are the same thing</div>
                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="true">B. Scope defines what you can do; standards define how well you should do it</div>
                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">C. Scope applies to nurses; standards apply to medical assistants</div>
                                <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">D. Standards are set by the state; scope is set by the employer</div>
                            </div>
                            
